President Joe Biden visited Germanna Community College in Culpeper, Virginia to discuss lowering the cost of healthcare and prescription drugs. He highlighted the high cost of prescription drugs in the United States compared to other countries and the financial burden it places on Americans. Biden proposed allowing Medicare to negotiate drug prices and capping out-of-pocket expenses for seniors on Medicare. He also emphasized the need for transparency in healthcare costs and the enforcement of laws that provide discounts on prescription drugs for rural clinics and community health centers. Additionally, Biden mentioned his efforts to address surprise medical billing and his commitment to making healthcare more affordable and accessible for all Americans.